# 📚 Literature Overview: SynapseStocks Dashboard & Layout Components

## 🧠 Conceptual Foundation

SynapseStocks appears to be a modular web-based analytics platform designed to deliver real-time insights into stock trends and agent-based decision systems. It leverages modern front-end technologies—React, React Router, and Material UI—to create a responsive and intuitive user interface.

This system can be conceptually aligned with **decision support systems (DSS)** and **agent-based modeling (ABM)** frameworks in financial analytics, where user interaction and visualization play a critical role in interpreting complex data.

---

## 📊 Dashboard Component: Literature Context

### 🔍 Theoretical Underpinning
The Dashboard component functions as a **visual decision interface**, allowing users to:
- Select pharmaceutical stocks
- Choose between buy/sell actions
- View agent-based insights

This aligns with literature on **interactive financial dashboards**, which emphasize:
- **User-centric design** for financial decision-making (Zhou et al., 2020)
- **Real-time data visualization** to support trading behavior (Chen & Lee, 2019)
- **Behavioral finance integration**, where UI elements influence user perception of risk and opportunity

### 🧪 Related Technologies
- **Material UI**: Used to create accessible, responsive components that follow Google's Material Design principles.
- **React Hooks**: `useState` and `useEffect` enable reactive data flows, a concept supported by declarative UI literature (React Docs, 2023).
- **React Router**: Enables modular routing, supporting the idea of **micro-frontends** in scalable web architectures.

### 📚 Suggested Readings
- [Beginning Azure Synapse Analytics - Springer](https://link.springer.com/book/10.1007/978-1-4842-7061-5) – for understanding data integration and analytics pipelines.
- [Interactive Dashboards in Financial Systems](https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0167923620301749) – explores how dashboards influence user decisions.

