## 🧭 Layout Component: Literature Context

### 🔍 Theoretical Underpinning
The Layout component serves as a **navigation shell** and **access control interface**, providing:
- Route-based navigation
- Session management via logout
- Dynamic rendering of nested views

This structure reflects principles from:
- **Single Page Application (SPA)** architecture
- **Role-based access control (RBAC)** in UI design
- **User experience (UX)** consistency through persistent layout elements

### 🧪 Related Technologies
- **React Router’s `<Outlet />`**: Facilitates nested routing, a key concept in component-based UI composition.
- **Material UI AppBar & Toolbar**: Implements persistent navigation, echoing design patterns from enterprise dashboards.
- **Logout Logic**: Implements client-side session invalidation, a common pattern in token-based authentication systems.

### 📚 Suggested Readings
- [Optimizing Facility Layouts for Efficient Operations](https://ijrar.org/papers/IJRAR23C2923.pdf) – while focused on physical layouts, the principles of optimization and flow apply metaphorically to UI layout design.
- [Azure Synapse Architecture & Analytics](https://hevodata.com/learn/azure-synapse-architecture/) – for understanding how layout and orchestration apply to data systems.

